


test - For the first tine only, use these two commands for setup, after git is installed:

$ git config --global user.name 'Pankaj Sharma'
$ git config --global user.email 'pankaj.sharma@gmail.com'

Go to the folder that you want to add to git and runn following command
$ git init

it will create a .git folder in the directory

Following command will add all the files in the directry to git staging area
$ git add <filename> or <.>

Following command tells whats been added to the git staging area
$ git status

Following command removes files from git staging area
$ git rm --cached <file name> or <.>

Following command commits changes to the git repo
$ git commit -m 'change text'

Run following command to connect with github repo
$ git remote add origin https://github.com/pankajsharma-source/account.git

Run following command to add code to the github remote repo
$ git push -u origin master
